# {{ service_name }} MCP — Deployment

## Local Development

```bash
cp env.example .env
# Edit .env with your values
python -m venv venv && source venv/bin/activate
pip install -e ".[dev]"
uvicorn asgi:application --reload --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8001 --lifespan on
```

Server starts at http://localhost:8001. MCP endpoint: http://localhost:8001/sse.

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Default | Description |
|----------|---------|-------------|
| `API_BASE_URL` | `https://api.example.com` | Upstream API URL |
| `AUTH_PROBE_PATH` | `/health/` | Endpoint to validate Bearer tokens |
| `AUTH_PROBE_ENABLED` | `false` | Enable token probe on SSE handshake |
| `MCP_PUBLIC_URL` | `http://localhost:8001/mcp` | Public MCP URL (shown in landing page) |
| `OAUTH_ISSUER_URL` | `http://localhost:8001` | OAuth issuer for RFC 8414 discovery |
| `OAUTH_AUTHORIZE_PATH` | `/o/authorize/` | OAuth authorize endpoint (relative or full URL) |
| `OAUTH_TOKEN_PATH` | `/o/token/` | OAuth token endpoint |
| `OAUTH_REGISTRATION_PATH` | `/o/register/` | Dynamic client registration endpoint |
| `OAUTH_SCOPES_SUPPORTED` | `read` | Comma-separated scope list |
| `LOGO_URI` | `` | Logo URI for OAuth discovery (optional) |
| `HOST` | `127.0.0.1` | Bind host |
| `PORT` | `8001` | Bind port |
| `LOG_LEVEL` | `INFO` | Logging level |
| `ALLOWED_ORIGINS` | `https://claude.ai,...` | CORS allowed origins |
| `TELEMETRY_ENABLED` | `true` | Enable JSONL telemetry |
| `TELEMETRY_HASH_SALT` | `` | HMAC salt for user-id hashing (set per-deployment) |

## Docker

A production-ready `Dockerfile` ships with the project.

```bash
docker build -t {{ project_name }} .
docker run --rm -p 8001:8001 --env-file .env {{ project_name }}
```

Override workers via `WORKERS` env (default 2). Container runs as non-root `app` user.

## Production (Render / Railway / Fly.io)

Set environment variables in your platform dashboard. Key production settings:

```
API_BASE_URL=https://your-api.example.com
MCP_PUBLIC_URL=https://your-mcp-server.example.com/mcp
OAUTH_ISSUER_URL=https://your-api.example.com
AUTH_PROBE_ENABLED=true
AUTH_PROBE_PATH=/health/
TELEMETRY_HASH_SALT=<32+ random bytes, base64>
HOST=0.0.0.0
PORT=8001
```

Start command (no Docker):
```
uvicorn asgi:application --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8001 --workers 2 --lifespan on
```

## Local debugging with MCP Inspector

The scaffold includes an `mcp.json` preset:

```bash
npx @modelcontextprotocol/inspector --config ./mcp.json
```

Set a Bearer token in the Inspector UI to exercise authenticated tools.

## Connecting to Claude

**Claude.ai (Web):** Settings → Connectors → Add → Custom → Web
- Remote MCP Server URL: `https://your-mcp-server.example.com/mcp/sse`

**Claude Desktop** (`~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json`):
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "{{ project_name }}": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "mcp-remote@latest", "https://your-mcp-server.example.com/mcp/sse"]
    }
  }
}
```

**Claude Code (CLI):**
```bash
claude mcp add {{ project_name }} --transport http https://your-mcp-server.example.com/mcp/sse
```
